review_blob: Pours clean and clear. Nice head...doesnt linger long though. Nice noble hop aroma. Taste is very malty and brady but the bitterness lingers just a touch...hangs around on the pallete. A nice beer but I prefer my lagers to demand me to take another swig. This does not do that. A tasty beer though.
Nice enough beer. Very pale and crystal clear. Always wary of beer in green bottles but no sign of being light-struck. An ok beer......just not that exciting. Many better German Pilsners out there.

Had this on tap in Port Campbell so no complaints about the location. The beer however is just ok. Nothing offensive but really lacking body, i.e. an overall watery impression.
The citrus, pineapple falvours advertised were very mild if that what they were shooting for.
Stouts can be quite generic and this is one of those. Nothing wrong but nothing special either.

By far the best of the Otway Prickley Moses beers I tried. Im a fan of an Irish red ale and this is a decent attempt. More body than the othe beers in the range and packs a nice overall, balanced flavour.
Just an ok beer. Nothing offensive but really lacking body, i.e. an overall watery impression.
Just an ok beer. Nothing offensive but really lacking body, i.e. an overall watery impression.
An interesting attempt but not one I would be rushing back for. Aroma is different but probably because you are looking for it. Not that keen on the after-taste as it tends to linger.
My favourite of Chimays offerings. Lovely citrus flavours that keep you wanting more. A bench-mark for the style.
Looks great with a creamy, coffe coloured head. Roast, coffee flavours with a nice mouth-feel. A good commercial example of a stout.

At 6%ABV this is not a Dopplebock and barely a Bock. That said it is a very nice and great value commercial offering. Nice colour with ruby hints, enjoyably malty although you would expect much more from a true dopllebock. Overall a very well balanced beer I thought.
Aroma is of watermelon which would be the yeast coming through, also some malt in the aroma. Mouthfeel is quite malty. A very enjoyable beer. Would happily purchase again.
Obviously Argentinas mass-produced lager. In no way offensive other than there are a million better more interesting beers to try. I would not buy again.
Not an overly interesting beer. A distinctive german taste but many better. Would not purchase again.
Great amber colour. Tastes like a dry-hopped beer. Not much aroma but great mouth-feel. Would buy again.
Not bad. Bit thin. Nice hop bitterness. Wouldnt purchase again. xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
I love the style and this is one of the best examples. Interesting to look at with a tall white head. A busy tasting beer that is sneakily refreshing. More please.
Just another mega-swill unfortunately. Not particular interested in brewed under licence beers.

I was lucky enough to win this at a MB event. Others thought it was the booby prize so I had low expectations. Well my opinion is this is a unique and magnificent beer. Unique flavour witha mouthfeel similar to champagne - very small bubbles though. I must remember to buy this again for a special occasion.
Not to be confused with Budweiser, this is a great beer. Rated it amongst the best at my one trip to BEERTOPIA.
This is fully-imported as opposed to brewed under licence and it shows. I really rate this beer, especially for the price. Mass-produced, etc... however it is a very tasty beer

I dont mind fruit beers, especially those that have been brewed specifically as one as opposed to has fruit added to mask a crap beer.
A good fruit beer must in essence be a good base beer, before any fruit is added. Cherries works for me and this would be my first choice of fruit beers.
Not a bad German lager. Many better to be had though. Brewed under licence in Australia - Im sure the original would be noticeably better.
I have enjoyed this beer on a number of occasions however the truth of it is it is largely uninspiring.
Judging from memory. Good solid pale-ale. Eye-catching colour, decent aroma for a bottled beer, tasty and very drinkable.
Typical Japanese lager. Quite refreshing, far from offensive but totally uninspiring. Sampled from a bottle at a Japanese restaurant in the city.
Very interesting beer. Loved the ruby colour. Would have liked more aroma and cant say I got much wine character, not that it was an issue for me. Overall an interesting beer.
beer_name: Saltram of Barossa Pepperjack Hand Crafted Ale

review_blob: As standard mass-produced pilseners go this was quite good  a hell of a lot better than V.B. put it that way. A small amount of noble hop aroma and taste sets this apart from other mega-swills. Purchased from IKEA of all places!
Not sure what BJCP style a Belgian Pilsner falls under so not sure if it is to style. That said it was a tasty beer, with noticeable spicy citrus flavors. Would be a good summer beer.
A standard mega-swill. Not offensive but very forgettable. Purchased from the Bottle-o in Box Hill.
Big bannana aroma and taste in this one. A great example of the style, however wheat beers are not really my go.
Is this a good example of an IPA - will have to try more. Very hoppy and bitter but a bit harsh for my taste.

Old Ale: Note - this must be drunk at the right temp. Straight out of the fridge I thought it was ordinary but as it warmed up I could taste a lot more in the beer. True to style and quite enyoyable to have one occasionally but not my favourite.
Huge saaz hop aroma and flavour in this pilsner. So much so its not really a session beer. Still I absolutely loved it and something to aim for when brewing this style.
At 9.2% ABV this beer is not harsh however it is just not to my taste. The bourbon aroma / flavour is just way too strong taking away any discernable porter qualities.
Very thin beer with an unenjoyable highly carbonated mouthfeel. I did not enjoy this porter at all.
beer_name: James Squire Jack of Spades Porter

review_blob: Very nice porter. Very strong chocolate and coffee flavours with a thick/creamy mouthfeel.
Magnificent beer. Best of the porters we had at our Melbourne Brewers tasting.

What a great dopplebock. True to style other than I couldnt get the strong malty aroma. Very smooth for a big beer and enjoyed the complex taste. Not something to have ten of rather one to savour. Definitely a style I will try other examples of and one to try and brew.
